) Command Code (CC) DUPED allows users to edit and correct information displayed by CC DUPOL, which contains information about each use of SSN ﬁled on tax returns. Records from current processing year on the Duplicate TIN Database can be added, changed and deleted (reversed). command code is intended for limited use only in situations where records the database cannot be corrected through the normal Mef and GMF update and reversal process. (
) The Display Record option displays all use of a SSN similar to CC DUPOL.
) The Add Record option in command code DUPED allows a record to be to the DUPLICATE TIN database. This option should only be used when a Form
X is ﬁled with additional dependents, or if a SSN use was missed during original GMF/M
processing. (
) The Change Record option allows a record to be updated if it has incorrect information. (
) The Delete Record option allows a record to be marked as reversed, so that the use of a SSN is removed. (

) The required input for CC DUPED is: a. Command Code Code DUPED b. Command Code Deﬁner (blank, A, C or D) Format c. Edited TIN (nnn-nn-nnnn) d. TIN Type Code (blank or *) e. Record Number (for deﬁner C & D only) (
) A DUPED command code with a blank deﬁner will display all uses of a SSN similar to the display of command code DUPOL. Code DUPED (

) In addition to displaying when, where, who used a SSN, and how it was Screens a RECORD NUMBER is displayed for every record that can be edited. (Reversed records cannot be edited.) A record number is required for each change or delete request, so the ﬁrst step in the editing process would be to display all the records using the blank deﬁner, and ﬁnd the right record to edit. (
) The status of an ITIN at the time it was added to the DUPTIN database will displayed in the Submission Site Literal area of the File Location Code. (
) From the display screen, enter the request type, record number and entry to edit a record. (
) Some of the features of the DUPED command code output display screens include: a. CC DUPED will provide IDRS-like paging when multiple pages exist. A maximum of
pages or

records will be displayed for a SSN. If there are more records than can be displayed, a ’nnn Prior records not displayed’ or ’nnn More records not displayed’ message will be in the ﬁrst & last page of the display. To display more records, enter another display request for the same SSN with a starting record in the command code line. b. The paging routine will automatically position the cursor following the Start of Message symbol. When the ENTER key is depressed, the terminal will display the next page or any page designated by a page number onto the format by key input. No entry key is needed move from one page to another. c. When a record has been edited, both the updated record and the record (marked as reversed) are displayed. If a SSN on a record has been changed to another SSN, a message indicating so will be immediately below the reversed record.

) To add a record, enter command code DUPED with a ’A’ deﬁner to display DUPED edit screen. The SSN should be researched ﬁrst to see if there DUPED additional uses of the same SSN. Fill in all the ﬁelds on the screen. Up to Tin Source Cd values can be entered to add multiple records for the same SSN. (

) When a record has been successfully added, the DUPED display screen be shown with the updated information and a ’REQUEST COMPLETED. RECORD ADDED’ message on the bottom line. The record will be added a priority code of blank because priority codes are not checked for manual entries. If the SSN was previously used as a Dependent or EIC by a primary SSN, an informational message ’DUPLICATE USE OF SSN’ will displayed instead. (

• The TIN source Cd ﬁeld will contain a single value. To change records for the same SSN, enter the other applicable TIN source in that ﬁeld. The data being changed will be applied to all the TIN source codes entered for that SSN that have the same Primary SSN and return ﬁling date. • To change the SSN of a record or to change a SSN from invalid to valid, the Name control is also required to be ﬁlled in for validation purposes. (

) When a record has been successfully edited, the DUPED display screen will be shown with the updated information and a ’REQUEST COMPLETED. RECORD CHANGED’ message on the bottom line. If the SSN was changed and also was previously used as a Dependent or EIC by a different primary SSN, an informational message ’DUPLICATE USE OF SSN’ will be instead. (
) To delete a record, enter command code DUPED with a blank deﬁner and original SSN from the ﬁled return to display all the records for that SSN. Code DUPED (

) Find the record number for the record that needs to be changed. Enter a ’D’ Records the request type and the record number in the record number ﬁeld. Also the entry code and hit transmit. This is equivalent of issuing another DUPED CC with deﬁner D and a record number. (
) The DUPED edit screen will then be displayed showing the record that is to deleted. Enter a ’Y’ at the prompt on the screen asking whether or not to delete the record. (
) When a record has been successfully deleted, the DUPED display screen be shown with the updated information and a ’REQUEST COMPLETED. RECORD DELETED’ message on the bottom line. (

) In the event of an error situation, one of the following messages will be a. DUPED REQUIRES AN EDITED TIN - The TIN must be entered as Code DUPED nn-nnnn. Messages b. DUPED DEFINER MUST BE BLANK, A, C, OR D- The deﬁner used invalid. c. NO RECORD FOUND IN TABLE - There is no information for the requested Taxpayer Identiﬁcation Number in the Duplicate TIN ﬁle. d. CHECK TIN AND RE-ENTER REQUEST - Check Taxpayer Number and re-attempt request. e. RECORD NOT FOUND - DUPED could not ﬁnd the record number entered to edit. Please check the record number and reinput. f. INVALID RECORD NUMBER - The record number entered for edit was invalid. Please check the record number and reinput. g. INVALID REQUEST TYPE - The request type was invalid. Must be A, or D h. INVALID DATA. PLEASE REINPUT- The data entered on the edit did not have an acceptable value. Please correct the ﬁeld and reenter. i. NAME CONTROL MISMATCH - The name control entered did not the SSN j. NAME CONTROL MISMATCH - NO SUCH SSN - The SSN cannot be found on NAP/INOLE. The TIN source Cd ﬁeld will contain a single value. To change records for the same SSN, enter the other applicable TIN source in that ﬁeld. The data being changed will be applied to all the TIN source codes entered for that SSN that have the same Primary SSN and return ﬁling date. To change the SSN of a record or to change a SSN from invalid to valid, the Name control is also required to be ﬁlled in for validation purposes.

When a record has been successfully edited, the DUPED display screen will be shown with the updated information and a ’REQUEST COMPLETED. RECORD CHANGED’ message on the bottom line. If the SSN was changed and also was previously used as a Dependent or EIC by a different primary SSN, an informational message ’DUPLICATE USE OF SSN’ will be displayed instead.
To delete a record, enter command code DUPED with a blank deﬁner and the original SSN from the ﬁled return to display all the records for that SSN.
